A police patrol team in Kwale Divisional Headquarters in Delta State has arrested a notorious armed robbery gang leader, Ossai Bright who allegedly specializes in robbery and snatching of motorcycles. The 21-year-old suspect was arrested along Adege street, opposite Ndokwa West Local Government Council while attempting to snatch a motorcycle, DAILY POST reports. The Police also recovered a cut-to-size locally made gun, a knife and one cartridge from the suspect. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Acting Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Edafe Bright. According to the Police image-maker,”Investigation is ongoing while frantic effort is in place to arrest other members of his gang.”